Came all the way from Staten Island to check this place out. Worth it! I walked in and the staff took my order quickly and respectfully and gave me my food in under 2 minutes. I got the Mix Over Rice (lamb and chicken). It was excellent; very well seasoned and and well portioned. There was way more meat than you would expect from a halal food tray and I love that. The sauces tastes balanced, just enough spice to keep it interesting but not enough to burn my tongue. Fries were crispy and nicely seasoned, and the salad was diverse, it was not just lettuce and ranch, it had more content than most other halal providers. They stopped indoor dining but they left a tent outside for roadside dining, and they have face shields for their workers, so I'd say they handled this pandemic very well. If you are ever on Steinway or even in Astoria I strongly recommend you check this place out. I will be coming back soon, God willing.

I noticed the way the place is designed, very spacious and fayroz I believe his name was called me over and handed me a menu. He told me the best burger here was the heart attack burger so I ordered it with bacon on top. It came with fries and a drink for $8!  Relive me when I tell you this burger was NOT DRY!!
